<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I2_FS_UsesTerminologies.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I2_FS_UsesTerminologies.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I2_FS_UsesTerminologies.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I2_FS_UsesTerminologies.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - I2 - Metadata - Resource adopts FAIR-supporting terminologies"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_I2_FS_UsesTerminologies"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_I2_FS_UsesTerminologies"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database, standard or policy resource adopts FAIR-supporting terminologies as curated by FAIRsharing. In FAIRsharing, this corresponds to the FAIRsharing record being linked to at least one FAIRsharing terminology artefact record. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the registry (e.g. FAIRsharing) record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

I2 requires that (meta)data use vocabularies that follow FAIR principles. This metric uses the relationships provided within FAIRsharing records to determine whether the resource adopts terminology artefacts represented within FAIRsharing. Terminologies are important FAIR-enabling characteristics because they provide shared meanings for concepts represented within data and metadata. The use of recognised terminology resources can improve consistency, interoperability, integration and reuse across communities. This metric supports FAIR Principle I2 by encouraging the use of terminology resources that may support FAIR use of the resource and its associated content."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/I2> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
    ftr:supportedBy <https://tools.ostrails.eu/champion>; 
    
    dpv:IsApplicableFor <https://vocabularies.coar-repositories.org/resource_types/c_1843/>;
    dcterms:creator <https://fairsharing.org/organisations/2281>; 
    
    ftr:hasBenchmark <https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/fair-assistance/fair-enabling-databases> ;
    
  
    ftr:hasBenchmark <https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/fair-assistance/fair-enabling-databases#fair-assessment-of-life-science-repositories-and-knowledgebases-benchmark-fair-ls-ark> ;
    
    
    
    
    
